               <person>
                  <persName role="owner" ref="PRS0000">The original donor(s) or commissioners may be those indicated in the prologue of the Vita (<locus target="4rb">4rb</locus>): Śahlä Rufāʾel, followed by a name which was erased with the exception of the last letter (b); his mother Walatta Qāl and his father Tasfā Mikāʾel. It seems that in many cases the second word in the rubricated name Śahlä Rufāʾel was later deleted and Śǝllāse was added instead (usually in black ink), to make Śahlä Śǝllāse out of it. In the same way, the name Walatta Qāl was transformed into Walatta Takla Hāymānot. &#xD;
Śahlä Śǝllāse, Walatta Śǝllāse, Walatta Takla Hāymānot, Walda Sǝmʿon  are mentioned in the supplication formulas on <locus target="29va">29va</locus>, 36ra, 43ra, 54rb, 73ra, 93vb, 99va, 106rb, 109ra, 110va and passim. In most of the cases the names are added in a different, somewhat later hand. On <locus target="129rb">129rb</locus>, an addition to the supplication formula indicates that Walatta Śǝllāse acquired the book with her own means.</persName>
